Breckenridge All-Sports Booster Club
August 12 at 9:00 PM ·

I can't believe we are weeks away from the start of the 2020 Buckaroo Football season!

Once again, the All Sports Booster Club will be putting together the annual Football Program. We are providing the opportunity for you to have your very own custom page to feature your child, business, or organization. 1/4 page ($50), 1/2 Page ($100), and Full Page ($150) spots are available. Deadline is Aug 28th.

Please print off the registration form below, or fill out the online registration here - https://bit.ly/BreckASProgram

All photos and graphics must be emailed to abcprintorders@gmail.com no later than Aug 28th.

Reach out to us through facebook or contact Ardes Johsnon at 805-603-9525, or Andy Rodgers at 940-452-8584 for more information.

post_text:
This week our special featured person is the Marcher of the Week!

Levi Adams was voted Marcher of the Week. Levi is a 14 year old freshman at BHS. Levi has been in the band for 3 years. He is in the pit and plays the keyboard/piano. In his free time, Levi likes to play the piano, which he has been doing for seven years now, and writing songs. Levi was chosen for his great work ethic. He is always present and attentive. He make sure everything is exactly where it is supposed to be and done as it is supposed to be done. Levi, while quiet, has a cheerful personality which is beneficial to the program. Levi is a huge asset to the BHS Band.

post_text:
It's time for our special featured person!

This week (Monday, October 28) our special featured person is the Marcher of the Week!

Sadie Bailey is this week's Marcher of the Week. Sadie is a 14 year old Freshman at BHS. She has been a part of the band for 3 years. Sadie plays the trombone. Sadie also enjoys doing crafts in her free time. She like working with clay and wire, etc. Sadie was chosen as Marcher of the Week, by the leadership team, because she works extremely hard each and everytime the band assembles. She does what she is supposed to do with no hesitation or discussion. Sadie is also a very kind individual. She treats other with respect and she is a very joyful person. She is a pleasure to be around. Congrats to you Sadie!

Shonda Wood is with Axel Puebla and 6 others.
October 23, 2019 at 9:57 PM ·

We have had a few people wanting to cheer the band on, as they leave for Denton on Saturday morning. It has been decided that individuals are going to meet at the pocket park (corner of Walker and North Breckenridge Ave) to cheer the band on, as they come through. We will be leaving the band hall as close to 8:30 AM as possible. The Fire dept and/or police dept will be escorting the busses on our way out. You have no idea just how much it would mean to these students to have some "fans" cheering them on. If you can spare a few minutes on Saturday morning, we would appreciate your support. Thanks!🎉🎉🎉

Please share to get the word out!

post_text:
Time for our special feature!

This week (Monday, October 21) our special feature is the Marcher Of The Week. This week the Marcher elected is Garrett Raymond. Garrett is 18 years old and a Senior at BHS. This is Garrett's 3rd year in band. He is in the pit, which mean he has a number of different responsibilities. Garrett enjoys video game design, in his free time. This honor was given to Garrett because he has done a great job of taken care of his responsibilities while also helping others. Garrett is always willing to help others with a wonderful attitude. Garrett is an incredible asset to the BHS Band.

Congratulations on great work!

post_text: It is that time of the week! Time to post our "Featured Person". This week (Monday 14) we are featuring our Marcher of the Week, Jaycie Hare. Jaycie is a Freshman and has been in band for 3 years. She plays the saxophone. Jaycie was chosen for Marcher of the week for being such a hard worker. She does a wonderful job for our band and for her section. I asked Jaycie if she had a hobby, she said that she doesn't know of a hobby but "she likes to make people happy". Very good Jaycie! Thank you Jaycie for all you do for The Pride of Breckenridge Marching Band. You are a great asset.

post_text:
Super proud of The Pride of Breckenridge Marching Band. We did get a 2 rating BUT
actually, we did amazing. The rating does not reflect our performance. No one in the contest received straight 1's. They use a point system and we actually won 1st out of 3A and we were 4th place, over all, in the entire competition. We rocked it and will bring it at the district competition next Saturday .

Photos will be posted by bedtime. 👍

post_text: If you are a parent or grandparent of a band member and have not "liked" the Breckenridge Band Parents Facebook page, please do so. We try really hard to do everything we can to make sure the students have what they need to do the best they can do, whether it be at football games, contests, or simply practice. We really could use some more parents helping with these meals and activities. If we all work together there will not be a burden placed on anyone. Thanking you in advance!

post_text:
It is now time for the special featured person!

This week our special featured person is the marcher of the week for the week of Monday, September 30th. We are so proud to announce that The Marcher of the Week is Spencer Ortega. Spencer is a 17 year old Junior at BHS. He has been in the Marching band for 4 years. He is in the percussion section and plays the cymbals. Spencer enjoys racing video games and dancing when he is not doing school work and band. Spencer was chosen for marcher of the week for his awesome skills and his work ethic. Spencer is so much fun to be around and loves to have a good time but also knows when it is time to go to work and at that point, he is all business. The band is so blessed to have Spencer. He is a crucial part of this team.

SHOUT OUT: Spencer also won “OUTSTANDING CYMBALS" in the Drumline & Pit Contest, held in Graham, over the weekend! We are so proud of you!

post_text:
Special featured Marcher of the Week!

Congratulations to Jose Mendoza for being Marcher of the Week for the week of Monday, September 9th. Jose is 14 years old and a Freshman at BHS. He plays the baritone saxophone. Jose was chosen because of his great work ethic and positive attitude. He is a wonderful asset to The Pride of Breckenridge Marching Band! Fun fact: The Marching Band is nothing new to Jose's family. He has a sister who graduated in 2018 and played the bass clarinet. At the present, Jose has two sisters in the BHS band. One is a Senior and plays the Vibraphone and the other is a Sophomore and plays the clarinet. He also has a sister in the BJHS Band. She plays the saxophone. The tradition will continue!❤

We are very proud of you, Jose!

post_text:
It is time for the "Featured Individuals" for the week of August 19th.

This week we spotlight The Pride of Breckenridge Marching Band's Drum Majors, Kolton Myers and Kayla Wood. These two work extremely hard to help bring it all together. There are many things that these individuals do that goes unseen to the public, but is necessary for the band to run as smooth as possible. Their positions require many things other than simply conducting the band, although they do that also. Both, Kolton and Kayla do their jobs very well and with pride! Our community is blessed to have these two representing The Pride of Breckenridge Marching Band, as the Drum Majors. If you see either of these students, please let them know they are appreciate.

*Their bios are in the photo caption.
(Personal information provided by each individual)

The special featured individuals for the week of August 12 are OUR AMAZING BAND DIRECTORS! We as a band, as a school district, and as a community are so blessed to have these two men directing "The Pride Of Breckenridge Marching Band"! These men are constantly teaching these students. They teach them many things about marching band and music but more importantly they are teaching them lessons about life. These lessons will be useful in all that they do. Please take time to let these two men know they are extremely appreciated!

post_text:
Update on my plans for this page.

I got some really good shots of the band tonight. We took a great group photo, which will be in the football program. I'll add it to this page after the first football game. Some of the other photos I took tonight will be added along the way. There will be a weekly featured individual(s). This week's main feature will be our amazing Band Directors! Check back tomorrow night for that. Next week will feature our awesome Drum Majors. Then, I'll cover our wonderful Color Guard. When the football games get started, our featured person of the week will be the "Marcher of the Week". There is a lot of fun stuff coming up throughout the next few months!

For now, here are just a few photos that the kids asked me to take tonight. I will be trying to get different students and sections each time I am at practice.

Have a great night!
